After removing the dependency on TaskType from TcpServer.cs, the AOT compilation worked successfully.

The threading top level documentation page shows really very helpful example code for using SemphoreSlim

```C#
using DotNext.Threading;
using System.Threading;

var semaphore = new SemaphoreSlim(0, 1);
var syncLock = Lock.Semaphore(semaphore);
var asyncLock = AsyncLock.Semaphore(semaphore);

//thread #1
using (syncLock.Acquire())
{

}

//thread #2
using (await asyncLock.AcquireAsync(CancellationToken.None))
{

}
```

But should it not be
```C#
...
var semaphore = new SemaphoreSlim(1, 1);
...
```

instead?

Initializing the semaphore with (0,1) creates an already "locked" semaphore.
